This paper presents a framework for exact discovery of top-k sequential patterns, which is a common problem in data mining and machine learning. The paper focuses on interestingness measures and employs a branch-and-bound algorithm for pattern discovery. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.DB (databases), cs.DS (data structures and algorithms), cs.AI (artificial intelligence), cs.LG (machine learning), and cs.IR (information retrieval).
